+# Infrastructure Dependencies Consolidation - Summary
+
+## Overview
+
+This document summarizes the infrastructure dependencies consolidation performed on the Apache ShenYu project. The goal was to centralize all infrastructure-related dependencies into a well-organized structure that ensures consistency, simplifies dependency management, and prevents version conflicts.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### 1. Created Infrastructure Dependencies BOM
+
+**File:** `/testbed/shenyu-infra/shenyu-infra-dependencies/pom.xml`
+
+A new Bill of Materials (BOM) module that centralizes version management for all infrastructure dependencies. This module:
+
+- Stands alone with Apache parent POM (avoiding circular dependencies)
+- Defines all infrastructure dependency versions internally
+- Groups dependencies by category:
+  - Service Discovery & Registry (Nacos, Eureka, Consul, Polaris, Apollo)
+  - Configuration Management (Zookeeper/Curator, ETCD)
+  - Messaging Infrastructure (Kafka, RocketMQ, Pulsar, RabbitMQ)
+  - Observability & Monitoring (Prometheus)
+  - Logging Infrastructure (Elasticsearch, ClickHouse, Cloud logging services)
+  - Container Orchestration (Kubernetes)
+  - Database Drivers (MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL, H2, OceanBase, OpenGauss)
+  - Data Persistence (MyBatis)
+  - Cloud Platform (Spring Cloud)
+  - Email Infrastructure (Jakarta Mail)
+
+### 2. Added New Infrastructure Configuration Modules
+
+Created three new infrastructure modules to provide configuration classes for key infrastructure components:
+
+**shenyu-infra-consul** (`/testbed/shenyu-infra/shenyu-infra-consul/`)
+- Configuration class: `ConsulConfig.java`
+- Properties: host, port, token, waitTime, watchDelay
+
+**shenyu-infra-apollo** (`/testbed/shenyu-infra/shenyu-infra-apollo/`)
+- Configuration class: `ApolloConfig.java`
+- Properties: appId, meta, env, clusterName, namespace, token
+
+**shenyu-infra-polaris** (`/testbed/shenyu-infra/shenyu-infra-polaris/`)
+- Configuration class: `PolarisConfig.java`
+- Properties: namespace, serverAddr, token, timeout
+
+### 3. Updated shenyu-infra Module Structure
+
+**File:** `/testbed/shenyu-infra/pom.xml`
+
+Updated the parent POM to include all infrastructure modules in alphabetical order:
+- shenyu-infra-dependencies (BOM)
+- shenyu-infra-apollo
+- shenyu-infra-consul
+- shenyu-infra-etcd
+- shenyu-infra-nacos
+- shenyu-infra-polaris
+- shenyu-infra-redis
+- shenyu-infra-x-module
+- shenyu-infra-zookeeper
+
+### 4. Updated Root POM to Import Infrastructure BOM
+
+**File:** `/testbed/pom.xml`
+
+Added the infrastructure dependencies BOM to the root POM's dependencyManagement section:
+
+```xml
+<dependency>
+    <!-- Import infrastructure dependencies BOM -->
+    <groupId>org.apache.shenyu</groupId>
+    <artifactId>shenyu-infra-dependencies</artifactId>
+    <version>${project.version}</version>
+    <type>pom</type>
+    <scope>import</scope>
+</dependency>
+```
+
+This ensures all modules in the project inherit the centralized infrastructure dependency versions.
+
+### 5. Created Documentation
+
+**File:** `/testbed/shenyu-infra/README.md`
+
+Comprehensive documentation explaining:
+- Module overview and structure
+- Usage guidelines
+- Benefits of the consolidation
+- How to add new infrastructure dependencies
+
+## Architecture Benefits
+
+### 1. Centralized Version Management
+All infrastructure dependency versions are managed in one place (`shenyu-infra-dependencies`), making it easy to:
+- Update versions consistently across the entire project
+- Track which versions are being used
+- Prevent version conflicts between modules
+
+### 2. Clear Separation of Concerns
+Infrastructure dependencies are now clearly separated from:
+- Application dependencies (Spring Boot, etc.)
+- Business logic dependencies
+- Framework-specific dependencies
+
+### 3. Improved Maintainability
+- Single location to update infrastructure versions
+- Clear dependency ownership (infrastructure team)
+- Easier to audit and track infrastructure changes
+- Better organization for large multi-module projects
+
+### 4. Consistent Behavior
+All modules using infrastructure components (Nacos, Kafka, etc.) are guaranteed to use the same versions, preventing:
+- Runtime incompatibilities
+- Subtle bugs from version mismatches
+- Dependency resolution conflicts
+
+### 5. Simplified Module POMs
+Individual module POMs can now reference infrastructure dependencies without specifying versions:
+
+```xml
+<!-- Before -->
+<dependency>
+    <groupId>com.alibaba.nacos</groupId>
+    <artifactId>nacos-client</artifactId>
+    <version>2.2.4</version>  <!-- Version specified in every module -->
+</dependency>
+
+<!-- After -->
+<dependency>
+    <groupId>com.alibaba.nacos</groupId>
+    <artifactId>nacos-client</artifactId>
+    <!-- Version managed by shenyu-infra-dependencies -->
+</dependency>
+```
+
