+## Migration Notes for Developers
+
+### For Existing Modules
+
+No changes required to existing modules. The BOM import in the root POM automatically provides version management for all infrastructure dependencies. Modules will continue to work with their existing dependency declarations.
+
+### For New Modules
+
+When adding infrastructure dependencies to new modules:
+
+1. Simply reference the dependency without a version:
+   ```xml
+   <dependency>
+       <groupId>com.alibaba.nacos</groupId>
+       <artifactId>nacos-client</artifactId>
+   </dependency>
+   ```
+
+2. The version will be automatically managed by the `shenyu-infra-dependencies` BOM
+
+### Updating Infrastructure Dependency Versions
+
+To update an infrastructure dependency version:
+
+1. Update the version property in `shenyu-infra-dependencies/pom.xml`
+2. Run the build to verify compatibility
+3. All modules using that dependency will automatically use the new version
+
+## Future Enhancements
+
+Potential improvements for the infrastructure consolidation:
+
+1. **Add more infrastructure modules** for other components (e.g., Kafka, RocketMQ, Elasticsearch configurations)
+2. **Create Spring Boot auto-configuration** for common infrastructure components
+3. **Add infrastructure health checks** and monitoring utilities
+4. **Develop infrastructure testing utilities** for integration tests
+5. **Document infrastructure best practices** and usage patterns
+
+## Conclusion
+
+The infrastructure dependencies consolidation provides a solid foundation for managing external infrastructure dependencies in Apache ShenYu. It:
+
+- Centralizes version management in a single BOM
+- Provides clear organization by infrastructure category
+- Simplifies dependency declarations across all modules
+- Ensures consistency and prevents version conflicts
+- Improves maintainability and auditability
+
+This consolidation aligns with Maven best practices and provides a scalable approach for managing infrastructure dependencies as the project grows.
