+# Apache ShenYu Infrastructure Module
+
+This module provides centralized infrastructure dependency management and configuration for Apache ShenYu.
+
+## Overview
+
+The `shenyu-infra` module consolidates all infrastructure-related dependencies and configurations into a single, well-organized structure. This ensures consistency across the project and simplifies dependency management.
+
+## Modules
+
+### shenyu-infra-dependencies
+
+A Bill of Materials (BOM) POM that centralizes version management for all infrastructure dependencies including:
+
+- **Service Discovery & Registry**: Nacos, Eureka, Consul, Polaris, Apollo
+- **Configuration Management**: Zookeeper (Curator), ETCD, Apollo, Nacos
+- **Messaging Infrastructure**: Kafka, RocketMQ, Pulsar, RabbitMQ
+- **Observability & Monitoring**: Prometheus, Elasticsearch
+- **Logging Infrastructure**: Elasticsearch, ClickHouse, Cloud logging services
+- **Container Orchestration**: Kubernetes client
+- **Database Drivers**: MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL, H2, OceanBase, OpenGauss
+- **Data Persistence**: MyBatis
+- **Cloud Platform**: Spring Cloud components
+- **Email Infrastructure**: Jakarta Mail
+
+### Infrastructure Configuration Modules
+
+Individual modules provide configuration classes and utilities for specific infrastructure components:
+
+- **shenyu-infra-apollo**: Apollo configuration center
+- **shenyu-infra-consul**: Consul service registry and configuration
+- **shenyu-infra-etcd**: ETCD distributed configuration
+- **shenyu-infra-nacos**: Nacos service registry and configuration
+- **shenyu-infra-polaris**: Tencent Polaris service mesh
+- **shenyu-infra-redis**: Redis cache and data store
+- **shenyu-infra-zookeeper**: Zookeeper coordination service
+
+## Usage
+
+### In Parent POM
+
+The root `pom.xml` imports the infrastructure dependencies BOM:
+
+```xml
+<dependencyManagement>
+    <dependencies>
+        <dependency>
+            <groupId>org.apache.shenyu</groupId>
+            <artifactId>shenyu-infra-dependencies</artifactId>
+            <version>${project.version}</version>
+            <type>pom</type>
+            <scope>import</scope>
+        </dependency>
+    </dependencies>
+</dependencyManagement>
+```
+
+### In Module POMs
+
+Individual modules can reference infrastructure dependencies without specifying versions:
+
+```xml
+<dependencies>
+    <dependency>
+        <groupId>com.alibaba.nacos</groupId>
+        <artifactId>nacos-client</artifactId>
+        <!-- Version managed by shenyu-infra-dependencies -->
+    </dependency>
+
+    <dependency>
+        <groupId>io.prometheus</groupId>
+        <artifactId>simpleclient</artifactId>
+        <!-- Version managed by shenyu-infra-dependencies -->
+    </dependency>
+</dependencies>
+```
+
+## Benefits
+
+1. **Centralized Version Management**: All infrastructure dependency versions are managed in one place
+2. **Consistency**: Ensures all modules use the same versions of infrastructure components
+3. **Simplified Updates**: Update infrastructure dependencies in a single location
+4. **Better Organization**: Clear separation between infrastructure and application dependencies
+5. **Dependency Conflict Prevention**: BOM import ensures compatible versions across modules
+
+## Version Management
+
+All infrastructure dependency versions are defined in the root `pom.xml` properties section and referenced by the `shenyu-infra-dependencies` BOM. This approach provides:
+
+- Single source of truth for versions
+- Easy version updates
+- Clear dependency overview
+- Conflict resolution
+
+## Adding New Infrastructure Dependencies
+
+To add a new infrastructure dependency:
+
+1. Add the version property to root `pom.xml`:
+   ```xml
+   <properties>
+       <new-component.version>x.y.z</new-component.version>
+   </properties>
+   ```
+
+2. Add the dependency to `shenyu-infra-dependencies/pom.xml`:
+   ```xml
+   <dependency>
+       <groupId>com.example</groupId>
+       <artifactId>new-component</artifactId>
+       <version>${new-component.version}</version>
+   </dependency>
+   ```
+
+3. (Optional) Create a new configuration module under `shenyu-infra/` if needed
+
